Here's exactly what gets added after the existing `aws_iam_role_policy_attachment` block:

```hcl
resource "aws_iam_role_policy" "lambda_s3_put" {
  name = "${var.lambda_name}-s3-put"
  role = aws_iam_role.lambda_exec.id

  policy = jsonencode({
    Version = "2012-10-17"
    Statement = [{
      Effect   = "Allow"
      Action   = "s3:PutObject"
      Resource = "arn:aws:s3:::${var.bucket_name}/events/*"
    }]
  })
}
```

This:
- Creates an inline policy attached directly to the Lambda execution role
- Grants `s3:PutObject` scoped to only the `events/` prefix in the app bucket (not the entire bucket)
- Uses `var.bucket_name` so it automatically targets the correct bucket per deployment
